Q6 
Write a program that asks the user for a whole number and then iterates through all numbers from 1 up to that number and calculates the total sum of all these numbers and prints the total at the end (e.g. 1 + 2 + 3).
Hint: You will need to create a variable that keeps track of the running sum of these numbers (i.e. this variable will be updated each iteration) 

num = input("Enter a number: ") 
sum = 0 
for i in range(1, num): 
  sum += i 
print(sum) 
